# iPhone Shortcut: yellowCircle SSH Command
# Import this into iOS Shortcuts app

Name: yellowCircle Command
Icon: Terminal (orange)
Color: Orange

---

## Shortcut Actions:

### 1. Ask for Input
Type: Menu
Prompt: "What command?"
Choices:
  - WIP Sync
  - Deadline Alerts
  - Blocked Tasks
  - Weekly Summary
  - Full Sync
  - Run All

### 2. Set Variable
Name: command_name
Value: [Based on menu choice]
  - WIP Sync → wip:sync
  - Deadline Alerts → alerts:deadline
  - Blocked Tasks → alerts:blocked
  - Weekly Summary → summary:weekly
  - Full Sync → sync
  - Run All → test:all

### 3. Run Script Over SSH
Host: [YOUR_MAC_IP]  # e.g., 192.168.1.100 or mac-mini.local
Port: 22
User: [YOUR_MAC_USERNAME]  # e.g., christopherwilliamson
Authentication: Password or Key
Script:
```bash
cd ~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/CC\ Projects/yellowcircle/yellow-circle/.claude/automation
npm run [command_name]
```

### 4. Set Variable
Name: output
Value: [Shell Script Result from step 3]

### 5. Show Notification
Title: ✅ Command Complete
Body: [output variable]

---

## How to Import:

1. Open Shortcuts app on iPhone
2. Tap + to create new shortcut
3. Add actions as described above
4. Replace [YOUR_MAC_IP] and [YOUR_MAC_USERNAME]
5. Test with "WIP Sync" option

---

## Siri Integration:

After creating shortcut, add to Siri:
- Settings → Siri & Search → Shortcuts
- Find "yellowCircle Command"
- Tap "Add to Siri"
- Record phrase: "yellowCircle Command"

Now you can say:
"Hey Siri, yellowCircle Command"
